ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Combating Chronic Absenteeism in Schools; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, chronic absenteeism impacts over 21.7 percent of students in Georgia; and
4 WHEREAS, students who experience chronic absenteeism are more likely to fall behind in
5 their academic work, face higher dropout rates, and struggle with long-term success in both
6 education and future employment; and
7 WHEREAS, absenteeism can be caused by a variety of factors, including, but not limited to,
8 health issues, family instability, socioeconomic barriers, transportation difficulties, and
9 school climate concerns; and
10 WHEREAS, addressing chronic absenteeism requires a collaborative and multifaceted
11 approach that involves school administrators, educators, parents, policymakers, and
12 community organizations; and
13 WHEREAS, research has shown that early intervention and targeted support programs can
14 significantly reduce chronic absenteeism and its negative effects; and
